    <exercise id="fs-id2721624" type="problem-exercises"><problem id="fs-id2721625">    <para id="import-auto-id2573635">Find the rest energy in joules and MeV of a proton, given its mass is <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mtext>.</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mtext>67</m:mtext><m:mo stretchy="false">×</m:mo><m:msup><m:mtext>10</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo><m:mtext>27</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:msup></m:mrow><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mtext> kg</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow></m:semantics></m:math>.</para></problem></exercise>
    <exercise id="fs-id2681831" type="problem-exercises"><problem id="fs-id2573985">    <para id="import-auto-id2644941">If the rest energies of a proton and a neutron (the two constituents of nuclei) are 938.3 and 939.6 MeV respectively, what is the difference in their masses in kilograms?</para>
