    <exercise id="fs-id2911245" type="problem-exercises"><problem id="fs-id2911246">    <para id="import-auto-id2502156">(a) Using data from <link document="m60912" target-id="import-auto-id2866785"/>, find the mass destroyed when the energy in a barrel of crude oil is released. (b) Given these barrels contain 200 liters and assuming the density of crude oil is <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mn>750 kg</m:mn><m:msup><m:mtext>/m</m:mtext><m:mn>3</m:mn></m:msup></m:mrow></m:semantics></m:math>, what is the ratio of mass destroyed to original mass, <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mn>Δ</m:mn><m:mi fontstyle="italic">m</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">/</m:mo><m:mi>m</m:mi></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{Δm/m} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>?</para></problem>
<solution id="fs-id3165931">
    <para id="import-auto-id2923850"><m:math>
        <m:semantics>
          <m:mrow>
            
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>6</m:mn>
                  <m:mtext>.</m:mtext>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mtext>56</m:mtext>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">×</m:mo>
                    <m:msup>
                      <m:mtext>10</m:mtext>
                      
